(1190, 'As he continued to grow, his mother used wagon wheels for buttons on his shirts. No bed could ..... his size, so Paul contentedly slept outdoors, under the stars.', 'maximize', 'Correlate', 'instigate', 'accommodate', 'admin', 0, 4, 2),
(1191, 'In one of the coldest winters on record, he found a baby ox in the snow. The ..... conditions had turned the ox so blue, that even after he was thawed out, the color never changed.', 'harmonious', 'tropical', 'hostile', 'favorable', 'admin', 0, 3, 2),
(1192, 'Paul named the ox, \"Babe\" and they were constant companions. Babe had such a ..... appetite; he could eat 30 bales of hay, with the wire still on them.', 'repetitive', 'discrete', 'miniscule', 'voracious', 'admin', 0, 4, 2),
(1193, 'Paul and Babe were a great team; no obstacle was too big for them to tackle. In fact, when settlers complained about a ..... crooked road, Paul hitched Babe to a yoke and straightened it out.', 'meandering', 'mesmerizing', 'smooth', 'level', 'admin', 0, 1, 2),
(1194, 'Loggers liked to wear their hair and beards long to stay warm in the winter, and then cut them off in the spring. One year, the winter lasted so long; the loggers had to tuck their beards in their boots. Finally, they cut them off with a ......', 'scythe', 'pitchfork', 'shovel', 'griddle', 'admin', 0, 1, 2);
