(1195, 'Winters in Minnesota came suddenly. One year, as the loggers were drinking coffee, it got so cold, the drinks instantly became ......', 'mufflers', 'popsicles', 'unmanageable', 'forgettable', 'admin', 0, 2, 2),
(1196, 'The same winter, there was so much snow in Minnesota; the men had to dig down 20 feet to find the tops of the trees. When it all melted, the snow created the Great Lakes region and a new ..... area stocked with snow-fish.', 'cay', 'peninsula', 'playground', 'ecological', 'admin', 0, 4, 2),
(1197, 'The tall tales of Paul Bunyan\'s fantastic existence will always delight readers with their amazing ..... They can even view an 18 foot tall statue of the King of Lumberjacks next to Babe, the Blue Ox on the shore of Lake Bemidji, Minnesota.', 'accomplishment', 'incredible', 'embellishments', 'exaggeration', 'admin', 0, 3, 2);
